phase2.explanation:
You tried to create a Player with parameters, but the class doesn't have a constructor that accepts them.

**The fix:**
```csharp
public class Player
{
    public string name;
    public int health;

    // Add a constructor!
    public Player(string playerName, int startingHealth)
    {
        name = playerName;
        health = startingHealth;
    }
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"If you need to pass data when creating an object, you need a constructor. It's the setup method for your class."
